channel.title: ServerSoft
channel.description:
[hr][size=10pt]Welcome to the [b]ServerSoft Development Team[/b] thread, Version [b]3.5B[/b][/size][hr] [sup]We have a variety of titles you can choose from that best fits your description![/sup]
[ul][li]Introduction to ServerSoft.[/li] [li]Positions and Titles.[/li] [li]Development Team.[/li][/ul]
[hr]
[size=15pt][b]Introduction to ServerSoft[/size]
ServerSoft is a fast-growing Private-Server community of the [b]508 Division[/b]. We have different bases throughout different areas, including on the internet. We have teams that help make this community fast growing as it is, and well respected. We are recruiting experienced members of programming as well as RuneScape. Why don't you check out the next few chapters to learn more about this opportunity and the rewards that may follow.
[hr][sup]ServerSoft was first created in January of 2007. We were small then. Three years later we've put are skills to the max and we've become three in one.[/sup]
[size=15pt][b]Positions and Titles[/size]
There's a variety of Task Positions and Titles that you can choose from that best fits your description. Each position has a certain task or asignment of it's own and will pay upon it's difficulty. View the list below for a list of positions you can choose from and a description that best fits it's title:
[ol][li]Jr. Server Programmer [i]- Someone who helps program files for the server that has little or no prior experience.[/i][/li] [li]Sr. Server Programmer [i]- Someone who helps program advanced files for the server that has enough experience to fullfil his or her duty.[/i][/li] [li]Client Programmer [i] - Develop the Client by adding or editing the cache, editing source code, and adding additional files for further updates.[/i][/li] [li]Bug Reporter [i]- Report ALL Bugs noticable or seen, to appropriate authority. This requires glitch or hacking experience.[/i][/li] [li]Article Writer [i]- Write News Articles on our Website about new updates or changes to the server, with pictures included.[/i][/li] [li]Web Designer [i]- Design code such as PHP, or HTML for editing and modifying websites or forums. *Must have prior experience.[/i][/li][/ol]
Take your time viewing the titles listed above. It may take you awhile to decide which title to stick with. Here's a little [b][i]reminder[/b]: For each title you choose to work with, you can also get promoted on that title to a higher rank! So there won't be any need having two titles, or quitting one title to switch over to the other. This will make the process much more easier. After you select your appropriate title, you might need to learn some information about [b]Development Teams[/b].
[hr][sup]Each position will have it's own pay. You will get payed for working for us, through [i]Gift Cards, Ultimate Game Cards,[/i] or[i] RuneScape Cards.[/i][/sup]
[size=15pt][b]Development Teams[/size]
With all Title Positions put together, they form the [i]Development Team[/i]. We use these developments together to form [b]ServerSoft[/b]. Once you have your selected title, and have had it confirmed with ServerSoft for you to be a Valid SSDT Member, you will have to register for a Server Account. The Account will be of Administrator status, most will often be hidden Admin. You will have FREE Commands and full server benefits. You will also be e-mail monthly a FREE Giftcard, Ultimate Game card, or RuneScape card for your services with ServerSoft. We ask of that when you register to become a member that you use true, valid Identity Credentials otherwise you will be banned from registering.
Use the form below to verify your information:
[code] Name: Age: Experience: Location: Desired Title: If given a file to code, when will you have it done by (Deadline): When is the best time for you: About you: [/code]
[hr]
[sup]Post or Send me a message whenever you feel like it, with the required information if you wish to join.[/sup]
[b]Post or PM your suggestions or ideas to this new Project of Development. Use: [code] Name: Age: Experience: Location: Desired Title: If given a file to code, when will you have it done by (Deadline): When is the best time for you: About you: [/code]
To verify information if you wish to register a position, you can just simply post a comment and it will soon be read. Thank you, in regards, Questmaster 2k10.

When is the best time for you: Wed-Sun between 4-11pm, but you can reach me at anytime on MSN.

About you: Here’s some info about me I’m 16 years old I’m in 10th grade at high school this year I’m taking computer development classes as well as web page designing I’m also a varsity wrestler. I like servers where the staff talks to there players an everyone knows each other an gets a long that makes the community grow an more fun for the players an I know some ways to make a server like that. I’m a facilitator I will do anything that you give me an I’ll give 110% effort all the time even if I don’t know how to do w/e is I’ll find out how to do it. I’m also an idealist I have some good Ideas for servers and economys so just message me let me know what you need an I’ll try my best to do it I only do 317 server coding so anything other than 317 don’t ask me I’m also not good with regardless clients.

Contact Info: teacupcoder@live.com
